<DetailPostLayout
  title="Bucketheads"
  description="A mobile game designed to help people raise their media literacy through mini-games."
  keywords="mobile game, media literacy, fake news, educational game, UX design, game design"
>
  <div class="post">
    <main class="post-wrapper">
      <DetailHeader
        tag="GAME DESIGN"
        description="Aug-Dec 2019">
        <h1 class="font-type">
          Bucketheads
        </h1>
        <p class="project-subtitle">A mobile game to raise media literacy through engaging mini-games.</p>
      </DetailHeader>

      <section class="buckethead-content">
        <figure class="figure hero-figure">
          <img src="https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/61e1afcc293eac3233b2e17f/61e2035537e2df8ed69f3d9f_main.jpg" alt="Landing page of the game" />
        </figure>

        <div class="content-section first">
          <div class="section-heading">
            <span class="section-number">01</span>
            <h2>Project Overview</h2>
          </div>
          <p class="intro-paragraph"><strong>Bucketheads</strong> is a mobile game concept designed to help people improve their media literacy in a fun and engaging way. It consists of a series of fast-paced mini-games, each designed to teach a core skill for consuming news critically and identifying misinformation.</p>
          
          <div class="card-grid two-cols">
            <div class="info-card">
              <h4>The Goal</h4>
              <p>Our primary goal was to develop an effective and enjoyable solution in the fight against fake news. We chose to create an educational mobile game that promotes media literacy skills without feeling like a traditional lesson.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
              <h4>My Role</h4>
              <p>As the <strong>Game Designer and UX Developer</strong>, I researched the key elements of media literacy and translated them into game concepts. I also planned, organized, and conducted user tests with over 30 students at Oulu International School to gather crucial feedback.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

<div class="content-section">
  <div class="section-heading">
    <span class="section-number">02</span>
    <h2>Gameplay & Core Mechanics</h2>
  </div>
 <p>In the game, the player cycles through mini-games in a random order. The difficulty level increases as the player progresses. The game ends when the player fails three mini-games. Each mini-game is built around a specific media literacy concept, such as identifying fake URLs, spotting manipulated images, or recognizing biased language.</p>
  
